<p class="govuk-body">This pattern lets the user add information with more than one part to a list.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="when-to-use">When to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Use this pattern when the user needs to add information with more than one part to a list. For example, when they need to enter more than one address or more than one person’s details.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="when-not-to-use">When not to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Do not use this pattern when the user needs to add different kinds of information that do not relate to each other.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="how-it-works">​How it works</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Allow the user to:</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>view a summary of what they have added to the list</li>
  <li>add things to the list</li>
  <li><a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/design/check-your-answers-pages">check their answers</a></li>
  <li>change things on the list</li>
  <li>remove things from the list</li>
</ul>

